   <text>
      <body>
         <pb facs="1874_10_26_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Buchheister_Shanghai_1.tif" n="1"/>
         <p>
            <seg rend=" left">
               <del rend="overstrike">
                  <hi rend="print">J. J.</hi>
               </del>
               <orgName type="firm" ref="K01116">
                  <hi rend="print">BUCHHEISTER.</hi> +C<hi rend="superscript">o.</hi>
               </orgName>
               <lb/>
               <hi rend="print">
                  <placeName ref="K00503">SHANGHAI</placeName>
               </hi>
            </seg>
            <seg rend="right">
               <date when="1874-10-26">26 October 1874</date>
            </seg>
            <lb/>
            <seg rend="center">Messrs <orgName type="firm" ref="K01004">L. Kniffler
                        +Co</orgName>
               <lb/>
               <placeName ref="K00514">Nagasaki</placeName>.</seg>
            <lb/> Dear Sirs,<lb/> We are in receipt of you favors of the<lb/>
            <date when="1874-10-11">11<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.</date> + <date when="1874-10-20">20<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. October</date> and regret to
                be obliged to inform you<lb/> that our purchaser for your steamers preferred to give
                us<lb/> an order to have a steamer constructed in <placeName ref="K00589">Scotland</placeName>,<lb/> about 30 feet longer + of much greater capacitiy,
                but which accor-<lb/> ding to telegraphic advice will nevertheless not cost
                more<lb/> than the price you asked for the <name type="ship" ref="K01787">Kobe' +
                    Victoria</name>.<lb/> Had the steamer been here they would, to my firmed<lb/>
                belief, been settled at once, but often the first excitement<lb/> about a war with
                Japan was over, the Chinese were no<lb/> longer in a great hurry and could afford to
                wait a year<lb/> to get a new Steamer out from home.<lb/> We are nevertheless
                keeping the 2 steamers constantly<lb/> in mind and would therefore be obliged by you
                letting us know<lb/> as soon as any change in your dispositories should take
                place.<lb/> Your Invoice +<unclear reason="eccentric_ductus">Bst</unclear> for
                    <measure type="volume" quantity="200" unit="bags" commodity="sulfur">200</measure> bags <term type="goods" ref="K01681">Sulphur</term> per “<name type="ship" ref="K01831">Essen</name>” to<lb/> hand + your draft against same 
                <hi rend="underline">T<hi rend="superscript">
                  <unclear>u</unclear>
               </hi>. 275.65.</hi> paid on<lb/> presentation. Please to ship balance as soon
                as<lb/> possible.<lb/> Is there no chance of chartering a vessel for<lb/>
            <placeName ref="K00528">Hakodadi</placeName> on the conditions explained
                previously.- </p>
         <pb facs="1874_10_26_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Buchheister_Shanghai_2.tif" n="2"/>
         <pb facs="1874_10_26_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Buchheister_Shanghai_3.tif" n="3"/>
         <p>
            <seg rend="center">
               <hi rend="underline">2</hi>
            </seg>
            <lb/>
            <seg rend="left">
               <del rend="overstrike">
                  <hi rend="print">J. J.</hi>
               </del>
               <orgName type="firm" ref="K01116">
                  <hi rend="print">BUCHHEISTER.</hi>+Co</orgName>
               <lb/>
               <hi rend="print">
                  <placeName ref="K00503">SHANGHAI</placeName>
               </hi>
            </seg>
            <lb/> We made an offer to the ”<name type="ship" ref="K01788">Condor</name>” but her
                agents<lb/> did not accept the same. Please to let us know<lb/> whether there are
                always <measure type="volume" quantity="300" unit="tons" commodity="coal">3</measure>-<measure type="volume" quantity="400" unit="tons" commodity="coal">400</measure> tons of <hi rend="underline" n="2">N<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>. 1</hi> Karats<lb/>
            <term type="goods" ref="K01501">Coals</term> to be had in <placeName ref="K00514">Nagasaki</placeName>; so that a vessel chartered<lb/> here could be loaded
                without loss of time.<lb/> Do you know of any <term type="goods" ref="K01789">
               <hi rend="underline">big</hi> guns</term> for<lb/> sale in <placeName ref="K00514">Nagasaki</placeName> or other ports of <placeName ref="K00502">Japan</placeName>? If so<lb/> please send particulars.<lb/>
            <seg rend="right">Yoursfaithfully<lb/>
               <orgName type="firm" ref="K01116">Buchheister+C<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>
               </orgName>
            </seg>
            <seg rend="left">Mex<hi rend="underline">$ 74<hi rend="superscript">775.</hi>
               </hi>
            </seg>
         </p>
         <pb facs="1874_10_26_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Buchheister_Shanghai_4.tif" n="4"/>
